          Top Things to Do in Miami, FL

          Miami, a city known for its bright skies, warm climate, and sparkling beaches, is full of adventures just waiting for you. Look no further for all the fun things to do in Miami — water sports, sightseeing, nightlife, and more. We have a range of offers from incredible vendors right here on Groupon.

          Experience Miami with Exciting Deals and Offers

          Miami is a vibrant destination with fun activities and attractions, stunning beaches, lively nightlife, and a diverse cultural scene. Browse Groupon to find inspiration for things to do in Miami. It has exciting offers on tickets and events, outdoor activities, sightseeing tours, and more. Whether you’re catching up with friends or want a creative date night with someone special, we’re your go-to platform for exploring the “Magic City.”

          Adventures and Attractions for All Ages

          Thrilling water sports. Serene beach days. Captivating cultural experiences. Exquisite dining. Everyone can find fun things to do in Miami. Popular activities that appeal to all ages include marveling at marine life at the Seaquarium, seeing animals up close at Zoo Miami, going on a safari adventure at Everglades Safari Park, or riding a wave at one of the city’s many water parks. Try paintball, laser tag, mini golf, or bowling for even more kids' activities. Or you can hit the arcade. One thing is sure: You’ll never run out of family-friendly fun in Miami.

          Thrilling Water Sports and Excursions

          If you're a thrill seeker looking for fun things to do in Miami, water sports like Jet Skiing, parasailing, or deep-sea fishing will be hard to resist. Dive into the crystal-blue waters and experience a thrill like never before. If a serene aquatic experience is more your style, opt for kayaking or paddleboarding deals to explore the beautiful Biscayne Bay and its dynamic ecosystem. Or charter a boat for a peaceful sunset cruise. Browse Groupon to see what’s on offer before you go.

          Culinary Experiences and Nightlife

          With many multicultural food options, your list of things to do in Miami should undoubtedly include trying new cuisines. Explore Little Havana for authentic Cuban cuisine, Wynwood for trendy eateries and craft breweries, and South Beach for a mix of upscale dining and casual beachfront bites. If you’re a local (or just want to live like one), cooking classes and food tours offer a new way to delight your taste buds. Then, it’s time to experience the city's electric nightlife, with energetic clubs, laid-back lounges, scenic rooftop bars, and exciting live music shows. Miami's food and nightlife should not be missed, but with Groupon's offers, you don’t have to.

          Cultural Encounters and Museums

          If your ideal list of things to do in Miami leans toward cultural and educational experiences, check out the Pérez Art Museum for modern masterpieces, the Frost Museum of Science for the planetarium and tech exhibits, and the Vizcaya Museum & Gardens for historic beauty. Want to immerse yourself in real-world culture instead? Step into color with neighborhood tours that let you soak in Miami’s blend of cultures, from the history, architecture, and street art of neighborhoods like Little Havana to the famous Art Deco Historic District. You might find offers on museum admission, sightseeing tours, and more on Groupon, so check here first.

          Indulging Self-Care

          Looking to relax amid all the fun? Miami is the perfect place to find your zen. Sign up for yoga classes, spend a day at the spa, attend a wellness retreat, and more. Book a beauty treatment or sign up for a fitness class to see what the healthy side of the city is all about. Put a little self-care on your list of things to do in Miami.

          Frequently Asked Questions

          Miami is known for its beautiful beaches, so activities like swimming, sunbathing, or even surfing are popular. Relax on South Beach, explore the Miami Beach Boardwalk, and stroll through the lush Fairchild Tropical Botanic Garden. To get more active, visit the Everglades for airboat tours and wildlife spotting, kayak in Biscayne Bay, and bike along the Rickenbacker Causeway. Miami also has world-class golf courses and tennis centers for sports enthusiasts.
